                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002 Manchuria/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                            type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-16T17:00:00+00:00"
                            >March 16, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 16—1:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>111. Department’s 88, March 11, 1 p.m. On March 14th in reply to a question in
                    the House of Commons the Foreign Minister stated regarding <pb facs="0693"
                        n="589" xml:id="pg_589"/> the recognition of the Manchurian régime “our
                    present information would make it premature to take any such action.”</p>
                <p>In view of the fact that Washington correspondents of various newspapers report
                    the United States Government will not recognize the new régime, I made further
                    inquiry of the Foreign Office and was informed that the matter was still under
                    consideration by the legal department in view of the many attendant
                    complications. Foreign Office added informally [that] when any opinion was
                    provisionally reached they would consult with me before finally answering
                    suggestion presented as reported in my 107, March 12, noon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
